FT  08 JUL 93 / World Commodities Prices: Wool
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
With no wool being held in the main wool producing countries, prices are
static. In wool-using countries holidays are beginning to have their usual
effect, underlining dullness due to the recess in the wool selling season.
Sales from the Australian stockpile continue, at a low but not discouraging
rate, with the emphasis on superfine merino fleece but some support
elsewhere. The feeling is that at present wool prices production in primary
markets will decline more than already forecast. Recovery in the UK and US
economies is not seen as sufficient to offset recession in Japan and Europe
which used to buy large quantities.
