<TEXT>
KELSEY-HAYES, a unit of Varity, the automotive parts, farm equipment and
diesel engine maker, and Topy Industries, the Japanese engineering group,
are to set up a joint venture to develop, sell and distribute four-wheel
anti-lock brake systems in Japan and other Asian markets, Reuter reports
from Buffalo.
The joint-venture company will be named Topy/Kelsey-Hayes and each company
will hold a 50 per cent stake.
The venture is exclusively licensed in Japan and certain other countries to
sell Buffalo-based Kelsey-Hayes' latest EBC 10 family of anti-lock brake
systems for use on vehicles which are manufactured in those countries.
</TEXT>
