<HEADLINE>
FT  08 JUL 93 / UK Company News: Ford operations behind Vardy's rise to
Pounds 4.38m
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
REG VARDY, the multi-franchise motor dealer, increased its pre-tax profit by
nearly 11 per cent, from Pounds 3.95m to Pounds 4.38m, in the year ended
April 30 1993.
The main factor was a rise from Pounds 260,000 to Pounds 660,000 in the
contribution from Ford operations. The specialist division, where the market
saw a significant downturn, maintained its level of profitability.
There was no significant contribution from disposal of property. A sale was
expected during the year.
Sales totalled Pounds 205m (Pounds 178m) and operating profit came to Pounds
5.02m (Pounds 4.78m), with acquired operations accounting for Pounds 9.21m
(Pounds 9.43m) and Pounds 159,000 (Pounds 9,000) respectively.
Earnings per share were clipped to 7.1p (7.4p) and the final dividend is
2.9p for a total of 4.2p (4p).
Mr Peter Vardy, chairman, said five dealerships had been added to the group
since the beginning of May, and further acquisition opportunities were being
explored. There was almost Pounds 3m cash in hand.
</TEXT>
