FT  08 JUL 93 / Indian banker fired over scandal
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   NEW DELHI
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
India sacked the executive director of Syndicate Bank, one of the country's
largest state-owned banks, yesterday for his role in a Dollars 1.28bn
(Pounds 85m) securities scandal, the finance ministry announced, Reuter
reports from New Delhi.
Mr R S Pai, who was asked to go on leave last year pending investigations,
has been sacked with immediate effect, a ministry statement said.
Ministry officials later said an inquiry by the Reserve Bank of India, which
submitted its findings in May, found that Mr Pai had caused a loss of Rs2bn
(Dollars 64.5m) in portfolio investments.
