FT  08 JUL 93 / Bosnian Moslems set to reject plan
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   SARAJEVO
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Bosnia's Moslems looked set yesterday to reject a plan for a three-way
partition of the republic despite warnings from UN envoy Thorvald
Stoltenberg that this could threaten peacekeeping efforts there, Reuter
reports from Sarajevo.
The bulk of Bosnia's collective 10-member presidency met to consider a
report recommending formation of a federal state or protectorate under
international control. Both ideas would appear to be at odds with a joint
Serb-Croat proposal for a division into Serb, Croat and Moslem states.
