<HEADLINE>
FT  07 JUL 93 / UK Company News: Edmond shares fall on profit warning
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Shares in Edmond Holdings, the housebuilder, fell 4 1/2 p to 15p after the
company warned that profits for the year were unlikely to match current
market expectations.
Trading in the first half had been in line with expectations, in conditions
which had continued to be difficult. However, despite signs of recovery in
some geographical locations, the areas in which Edmond operates -
Humberside, East Anglia and south Wales - had not experienced any positive
effects and lower volumes and weaker prices had resulted.
The board did not feel it prudent to anticipate an improvement in trading
conditions in the near future.
In 1992 the company incurred pre-tax losses of Pounds 1.15m (Pounds 1.73m
profits).
</TEXT>
