<HEADLINE>
FT  07 JUL 93 / UK Company News: Avesco losses Pounds 0.2m below forecast
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
AVESCO, which serves the broadcasting, television and video markets, cut
pre-tax losses from Pounds 2.26m to Pounds 1.35m in the year ended March 31
1993.
The loss was also Pounds 200,000 below the forecast made with the Pounds 12m
rights issue in March.
Shareholders' funds had more than doubled and the group was in a much
stronger financial position, said Mr Richard Murray, chairman.
VideoLogic's planned expansion continued and its alliance with IBM to
produce low cost multimedia solutions had already resulted in the first
product, Mediator LC.
Each of the service businesses was profitable and their outlook for the
coming year was encouraging with growth expected in all areas.
AVS Broadcast, the television products operation, substantially reduced its
loss in the second half and should improve in the current year.
Turnover in 1992-93 expanded from Pounds 17.9m to Pounds 23.4m. To the
operating loss of Pounds 140,000 (Pounds 1.52m) VideoLogic contributed
Pounds 677,000 (Pounds 673,000), television products Pounds 558,000 (Pounds
709,000), and services division profit Pounds 1.05m (Pounds 164,000).
Discontinued activities accounted for losses of Pounds 5,000 (Pounds
202,000).
Losses per share came to 2.2p (3.4p).
</TEXT>
