<HEADLINE>
FT  07 JUL 93 / The Lex Column: Executive pay
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
As the last of the electricity companies finally brings down the curtain on
this year's main results season, an irritating trend is visible. Embarrassed
executives are increasingly refusing to discuss their pay when they announce
their preliminary results, arguing that the information will be disclosed in
the annual report.
Since most publicity is focused on the preliminary results, and annual
reports are not normally newsworthy, this is a pretty clear attempt to avoid
the limelight. Perhaps future artful dodgers will get the publicity which
their shyness and pay rises really deserve.
</TEXT>
